source.name: Measure 22 : Percentage of People with High Cholesterol that is Controlled | Income Level
source.description:
Poverty is defined by Census Bureau poverty thresholds. For more information on the definition of poverty, please see the Glossary under Help.

The red lines in the chart below indicate the confidence interval. The lower and upper confidence interval values can be seen in the table view. For more information on confidence intervals, please see the Glossary under Help.
